article.description: Christen Cunningham scored 18 points and Samford handled Florida A&M 86-67 on Saturday.
article.headline: Cunningham leads Samford over Florida A&M 86-67
article.linkText: Cunningham leads Samford over Florida A&M 86-67
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Christen Cunningham scored 18 points and Samford handled Florida A&M 86-67 on Saturday. Cunningham was 6 of 13 from the field and 5 of 6 from the line. Matt Rose scored 17 points, including four 3-pointers, and grabbed seven rebounds. Darius Jones-Gibson had 12 points and Marcus Johnson added 11, going 4 of 4 from the field. Samford (7-3) shot over 57 percent (30 of 52) and was 11 of 23 (47.8 percent) from beyond the arc. The Bulldogs outrebounded Florida A&M 35-28. Samford had 28 points off of turnovers and led in second-chance points 13-2. Treavann Warren and Justin Ravenal had 18 points apiece while Malcolm Bernard chipped in with 13 points. Ravenal made six of Florida A&M's seven 3-pointers on 10 attempts. Florida A&M never led and fell to 3-7.
